template.description: Create source docs for the CogStack Cohort tool.
template.name: CogStack_Cohort_create_source_docs

labels.label: Change the query and index name.
Step II: execute this only once. Currently this works with static file names that you have to declare in the "arguments" property."
Optional, change the minimum amount of files to be merged.

You MUST set/change the following parameters:
patient_id_field_name="patient" patient_ethnicity_field_name="ethnicity" patient_gender_field_name="gender" patient_birth_date_field_name="birthdate" patient_death_date_field_name="deathdate"
The source of the document id, always use the "meta.docid" or "meta.document_id_field" that you declared when annotating documents, the prefix will be cutoff, it must be the same field name as in the original patient record docs
annotation_document_id_field_name="meta.docid"
IMPORTANT: you may also need to set the date and time format. the fields that have dates in them should be the same format. Set via the "date_time_format" argument (Default: %Y-%m-%d).
Place these parameters in the "Command arguments" property, delimited by ";".
Modify the Query parameter to include/exclude fields, you should exclude the "text" field as you won't be using it here. For the samples DB, the text field is "document". Also the change index name.
Step I: grab annotations and records and pile them up creating separate dated JSON files.
